---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Pixelmix"
  description="About Pixelmix, the anime print shop."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
          <h1>One wall, one story at a time.</h1>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="factbox">
          <h3>At a glance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Founded</strong> — 2026</li>
            <li><strong>Focus</strong> — Anime & cinematic photography prints</li>
            <li><strong>Process</strong> — Curated, archival, signed</li>
            <li><strong>Shipping</strong> — Worldwide</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p>
            Pixelmix started as a folder of one person's favorite
            anime moments — the kind of frame that stops you scrolling.
            It's now a small shop dedicated to putting those moments
            on real walls, on paper that's built to last.
          </p>
          <p>
            We're not trying to be the biggest print shop. We're
            trying to be the one where every image is the right
            image. Two colors, one mood, one room.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every print is produced on archival paper with pigment
            inks, signed and numbered on the back, and shipped flat
            in a rigid mailer. Limited editions are limited; open
            editions are still individually numbered.
          </p>
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/gallery">See the work →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
